@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Main"

 Xit is an application that allows you to use the XPK package libraries in an intuitive
 way. Actually, Xit was written to replace XDrop by Martin A. Blatter which was issued
 in 1992. As a matter of fact, Xit is adding some new functionnalities to its 'ancester'
 XDrop.
 
 Functions of Xit:

 - Basic purpose : packing/unpacking of file(s) or drawer(s).
 - AppIcon / AppWindow.
 - Fast information about any present packing library.
 - Xit can pop up a window to show the evolution of the (un)packing.
 - A beep can be heard when the (un)packing is over.
 - The destination drawer for the packed files can be chosen.
 - You can choose either to keep or delete the source file.
 - The icon of the file is copied if present.
 - A default icon can be added if not present.
 - The user interface of Xit is MUI based. The windows can be easyly resized.
 - Easy install thanks to the Installer script.
@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@next "Registration"
@prev "Introduction"

 @{b}Needed Software@{ub}

 - Kickstart 2.0/Workbench 2.0 or more for the English version.
 - Kickstart 2.0/Workbench 2.1 or more for the other versions.
 - @{"MUI 3.1" link "MUI" 0} or more.
@endnode

